function count_model_rows(df_cars)
    return combine(groupby(df_cars, :model), nrow)
end
```

This function uses the `groupby` function to group the `df_cars` DataFrame by the `model` column. The `combine` function is then used to apply the `nrow` function (which calculates the number of rows) to each group, effectively counting the number of rows for each unique model value.
